paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: The paper discusses various variants of the TTR gene, particularly focusing on the wt-TTR and several mutants, including V122I, L55P, V30M, F87A, and T119M, along with their structural and functional implications.

individual_records.evidence_sentence: At 80 °C, wt- and mutant TTR complexes disassemble to form abundant monomers.
The F87A mutant completely disassembles to monomers and dimers at temperatures of ∼65 °C.
V122I has some low abundance of monomers throughout the temperature range examined.

functional_data.summary: The study investigates the structural and stability differences between wt-TTR and its mutants under varying temperatures.

variants.additional_notes: The paper discusses the stability of TTR variants under different conditions but does not provide detailed clinical significance for each variant.
